revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
{{never substitute}}
{{Lua|Module:Unsubst}}
{{Uses TemplateStyles|Template:Sfrac/styles.css}}
This template builds an alternative form of common or mixed [[fraction]]s, using a [[Vinculum (symbol)|vinculum]] (horizontal line), for [[Wikipedia:Manual of Style (mathematics)|scientific and mathematical text]]. It takes one, two or three parameters: the optional integer (may be signed), the optional numerator and the required denominator; in this order.

; <code><nowiki>{{sfrac|A|B|C}}</nowiki></code> : {{sfrac|A|B|C}} (integer, numerator and denominator)
; <code><nowiki>{{sfrac|B|C}}</nowiki></code> : {{sfrac|B|C}} (numerator and denominator)
; <code><nowiki>{{sfrac|C}}</nowiki></code> : {{sfrac|C}} (denominator only)

== Examples ==

<!--the fractions are separated by commas that are only visible to screen readers because they do not read out the space separators here-->

{{sfrac|2}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|4}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|6}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|6}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|6|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|9|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|11|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|13|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|15|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|22|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|1|1|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|16|2|3}}{{sronly|,}}{{sfrac|2{{pi}}|''a''<sup>2</sup>''b''}}

'''Inside the {{tl|math|...}} template (for inline math):'''

{{math|
{{sfrac|2}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|4}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|6}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|6}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|6|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|9|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|11|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|13|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|15|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|22|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|1|1|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|16|2|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2{{pi}}{{sronly|,}}|''a''<sup>2</sup>''b''}}
}}

'''Inside the {{tl|bigmath|...}} template (for standalone math):'''

{{bigmath|
{{sfrac|2}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|4}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4|5}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|6}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|6}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|4|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|6|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7|8}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|3|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|5|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|7|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|9|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|11|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|13|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|15|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|22|7}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|1|1|16}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|16|2|3}}{{sronly|,}} {{sfrac|2{{pi}}{{sronly|,}}|''a''<sup>2</sup>''b''}}
}}

== Parameters ==
{{TemplateData header}}
<templatedata>{
"description": "A template builds an alternative form of common or mixed fractions, using a vinculum (horizontal line), for scientific and mathematical text. It supports 1–3 anonymous parameters with positional meaning.",
"params": {
"1": {
  "label": "leftmost part",
  "description": "Denominator if only parameter supplied. Numerator if 2 parameters supplied. Integer if 3 parameters supplied.",
  "type": "string/line",
  "required": false
},
"2": {
  "label": "middle-right part",
  "description": "Denominator if 2 parameters supplied. Numerator if 3 parameters supplied.",
  "inherits": "1"
},
"3": {
  "label": "rightmost part",
  "description": "Denominator, always.",
  "inherits": "1"
},
"font-size": {
  "label": "font size",
  "description": "Set customized font size.",
  "type": "string/line",
  "required": false
}
}}</templatedata>

== See also ==
* [[Wikipedia:Rendering math]]
* {{tl|frac}}, displays common fractions using a [[fraction slash]]
* {{tl|BSsplit}}, for two lines of text, with formatting options
* {{tl|BScvt}}, for two distances
* {{tl|su}} ({{su|p=superscript|b=subscript}} text) – to align both b=subscript & p=[[superscript]]
* {{tl|sub}} ({{sub|subscript}} text) – to show a [[subscript]]
* {{tl|sup}} ({{sup|superscript}} text) – to show a [[superscript]]
* {{tl|sup sub}} (text{{sup sub|sup|sub}}) – for both 1=superscript & 2=subscript
* [[Help:Displaying a formula#Fractions, matrices, multilines]]
* [[Help:Convert#Fractions]]
* [[Number Forms]], a Unicode block consisting primarily of vulgar fractions
* [[OpenType]] fonts feature ''afrc'', [[CSS]] {{code|font-variant-numeric:stacked-fractions|css}} with little support as of 2020

